Verifies that class declarations are uniformly wrapped and indented.

== Properties ==

Default values appear <u>underlined</u>.

<h3>One-line Declarations</h3>
                <p>
                  The following properties refer to 'one-line declarations', i.e. declarations completely without
                  line breaks.
                </p>

<dl>
<dt>allowOneLineDecl = "<u>true</u> | false"
<dd>Whether to allow a complete class declaration in one single line. Example:
 public class Pojo { int fld; }

</dl>

<dl>
<dt>wrapDeclBeforeClass = "<u>always</u> | optional | never"
<dd>Whether to wrap class declarations before the <code>CLASS</code> keyword. Example:
 public static final
 class MyClass {

</dl>

<dl>
<dt>wrapDeclBeforeLCurly = "always | optional | <u>never</u>"
<dd>Whether to wrap class declarations before the opening curly brace. Example:
 public class MyClass
 {

</dl>

